<subSubSection pageId="136" pageNumber="533" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="136.[733,1326,2623,3046]" lastBlockId="136.[121,1327,3053,3479]" pageId="136" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[735,984,2895,2928]" pageId="136" pageNumber="533">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 62-89 mm, tail 4663-5 mm, ear 4-9 mm, hindfoot 11-16 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Blackish Whitetoothed Shrew is medium-sized to relatively large. Dorsal pelage is blackish blue or slate-gray, and ventral pelage is paler. Tail is ¢.75% of head-body length, hairy, and dark. Talonid of M? lacks fovea. There are three unicuspids.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="136" pageNumber="533" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="136.[121,1327,3053,3479]" pageId="136" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[122,233,3171,3204]" pageId="136" pageNumber="533">Habitat.</emphasis>
Mountainous regions in Angola, but there is no information related to habitat preferences of the Blackish White-toothed Shrew.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
